1- Use "pip3 install pipenv" to install "pipenv".

2- Use "pipenv shell" to setup your environment
and you will see the "Pipfile".

3- Use "pipenv install flask flask-sqlalchemy flask-marshmallow marshmallow-sqlalchemy"
to install the dependencies and you will see the "Pipfile.lock".

###################
# Activate venv
$ pipenv shell

# Install dependencies
$ pipenv install

# Create DB
$ python
>> from app import db
>> db.create_all()
>> exit()

# Run Server (http://localhst:5000)
python app.py

# Endpoints

    GET /product
    GET /product/:id
    POST /product
    PUT /product/:id
    DELETE /product/:id